-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dcl1665702806493.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dcl1665702806493.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dcl1665702806493.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dcl1665702806493\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define SOAP Properties\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define or edit the properties a web service component.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__p_d6500e1_d6501e1_d6502e1\">Typically, this form is used to examine or edit a web service signature that has been created by importing a WSDL file. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vmq1665702752774.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vmq1665702752774.html\" title=\"To call out to a web service, use the Uniface import facility (/sti /mwr =ws) from the Uniface command line.\">Calling Web Services from Uniface</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__section_oy1_dqf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1097615e70\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__ul_swm_dqf_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__li_d3173e1_d3174e1_d3175e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">URL of WSDL</span>—location of the WSDL\n          file. Normally, this is the URL but it can refer to a local copy of the file. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__li_d3176e1_d3177e1_d3178e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Port Name</span>—number of the web\n          server port </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__li_d3179e1_d3180e1_d3181e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Service Namespace</span>—namespace of\n          the web service </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dcl1665702806493__li_d3182e1_d3183e1_d3184e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Service Local Name</span>—name of the\n          web service </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tha1665702897542.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-Out from Uniface to a Web Service</a><p>A Uniface application can call a Web service via the Uniface SOAP connector.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8419409\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8419409\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define SOAP Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define SOAP Properties Define or edit the properties a web service component. Typically, this form is used to examine or edit a web service signature that has been created by importing a WSDL file. For more information, see Calling Web Services from Uniface . Fields URL of WSDL —location of the WSDL file. Normally, this is the URL but it can refer to a local copy of the file. Port Name —number of the web server port Service Namespace —namespace of the web service Service Local Name —name of the web service Related Links Call-Out from Uniface to a Web Service A Uniface application can call a Web service via the Uniface SOAP connector. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}